A chairde,

T=E1 s=FAil agam go bhfuil sibh go maith ar maidin!

Our 'Seanfhocal' for this week was: 'Aithn=EDonn ciar=F3g ciar=F3g eile'.
Literal translation =3D A beetle recognizes another beetle,"
Equivalent to English sayings like "It takes one to know one" or "Birds of =
a feather flock together," used to point out shared understanding, habits, =
or traits between people, often with a knowing, humorous, or sometimes dism=
issive tone.

Last night:

  *
We completed page 46 of the textbook, looking at 'Laethanta na Seachtaine' =
agus 'Uimhreacha'
  *
We then looked at the first 3 forms of numbers in the Irish language from 0=
-10 (PDF attached) - The Basic numbers, numbers used when counting things a=
nd the numbers used when counting people!
  *
We then completed pages 47-48 of the book practising our months of the year=
 and vocab related to Countries, before finishing off with the question 'Ca=
d as duit' =3D Where are you from and the grammatical structure that follow=
s the answer to that question (pg.48)
  *
We looked at 'An t-Ur=FA' (Eclipsis) and attached is a poem used to help re=
member what letters take an ur=FA and what Ur=FA that letter takes! - mB, g=
C, nD, dT, nG, bP, bhF.
We also watched this short clip that is often shown to students learning th=
e language to help them with the sound the nG ur=FA makes! https://youtu.be=
/IAHR1tk5xvU?si=3D-0fZCHaR-52tb9oa
  *
Ceacht 10.1 on page 49 was suggested for homework, as well as revising the =
numbers 0-10 in all forms!
  *
We finished up the class by looking through the attached document 'Is the F=
ada important in Irish' just to highlight some examples of how the fada not=
 only changes how a word is pronounced but also changes it's meaning entire=
ly!


  *
No class next Monday (02/02) due to the L=E1 Saoire Bainc (Bank Holiday)!
  *
Also attached is the list of class dates for semester 2 for those asking!
  *
Gaeltacht Trip: 17th-19th of April =96 Provisionally booked, waiting for co=
nfirmation from the office.

Go raibh m=EDle maith agaibh agus feicfidh m=E9 sibh i gceann coic=EDse (I =
will see you all in two weeks time!)

Le gach dea-ghu=ED,

Laoise Nic =CDomhair

Oifigeach Forbartha Gaeilge, Barr na gCnoc

Ionad na Gaeilge Labhartha  | Col=E1iste na hOllscoile Corcaigh | Corcaigh =
| =C9ire
